modules.description: Provides operations to manipulate a vector-like structure, including retrieving, setting, inserting, and deleting elements at specific indices. Works with a custom `t` type representing the vector and an `atom` type for element storage. Used to dynamically modify sequences in applications requiring indexed element access and mutation.

Provides operations to manipulate strings as sequences of characters, including accessing, modifying, inserting, and deleting elements at specific indices. Supports generating and applying patches to transform one string into another using the Wagner-Fischer algorithm, and merging strings with a conflict resolution function. Works with strings, individual characters, and patch structures to enable version control-like operations.

Provides operations for merging vectors using 3-way merges, computing diffs with the Wagner-Fischer algorithm, and applying patches to modify vectors. Works with arbitrary vectors, preserving structural integrity during transformations. Used in collaborative editing systems to resolve conflicts and synchronize changes across multiple users.

Provides operations to modify and compare vectors of atomic elements, including setting, getting, inserting, and deleting elements at specific indices. Computes and applies patches to transform vectors using the Wagner-Fischer algorithm for difference calculation. Supports three-way merging of vectors with custom conflict resolution.
